28. We recommended that management should initiate measures designed to come up with a Memorandum
of Agreement (MOA) with the GSIS defining therein the agreed balance of payables to the GSIS, if any, and
the terms and conditions in the settlement thereof. The following steps may help in facilitating
reconciliation of records.
a. Secure detailed profile of payables per GSIS records;
b. Reconstruct old GSIS accounts, if necessary, and update records;
c. Reconstruct old personnel profile, if necessary, and update personnel profile;
d. Counter-check GSIS records with the reconstructed and updated accounting and personnel records of
the LGU;
e. Negotiate with the GSIS for any differences that may be noted during counter- checking activity;
f. Enter into a formal agreement with the GSIS in the form of a Memorandum of Agreement (MOA);
and
g. Appropriate fund for the settlement of any payables to the GSIS as agreed in the MOA.

